  "summary": "## Summary: Fix AI Usage Widget Missing from Header\n\n### Changes Implemented\n- Re-added the `AIUsageWidget` import to `AppShell.tsx`\n- Re-added the desktop-only header bar containing the `AIUsageWidget` at the top of the main content area\n- The header bar is hidden on mobile (`hidden md:flex`) and shows the widget right-aligned with a bottom border separator\n\n### Files Modified\n- `components/ui/AppShell.tsx` — Added AIUsageWidget import and desktop header bar wrapping the main content area\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- The `AIUsageWidget` component (`components/ai/AIUsageWidget.tsx`) and API route (`app/api/ai-usage/route.ts`) were both intact — only the rendering in AppShell was missing\n- The widget is desktop-only (hidden on mobile via `hidden md:flex`)\n- The main content area is now wrapped in a flex column container to accommodate the header bar while preserving scroll behavior"
